# Cursor AI Assistant Rules for Touch Monorepo

## Server Management

- DO NOT start development servers - user manages their own instances
- Server runs on localhost:4040 (already running)
- Client runs on localhost:3000 (Vite dev server)
- Always test APIs with curl before making changes
- Never run `npm run dev`, `pnpm dev`, or similar commands unless explicitly requested

## Development Workflow

- Use `curl -s http://localhost:4040/api/endpoint` to test server endpoints
- Check server status with `lsof -i :4040` if needed
- The user handles server restarts and process management
- Focus on code changes, not server operations

## Project Structure

- Monorepo with apps/client and apps/server
- Shared packages in packages/
- Use TypeScript throughout
- Follow existing patterns and conventions

## Design System (Panda CSS)

- The Panda MCP server (`.cursor/mcp.json`) exposes tokens, recipes, patterns, breakpoints, and usage reports.
- For questions about breakpoints, tokens, recipes, variants, or design-system conventions, use the Panda MCP tools when relevant — no need for the user to ask explicitly.
- When working with recipes (cva/sva), follow existing patterns in the codebase; keep naming, structure, and variant conventions consistent.
